New Records: MacKenzie Gore achieved career-high innings (166 1/3) and career-high strikeouts (181) in the 2024 season.
Key Match Events: MacKenzie Gore pitched six scoreless innings, striking out nine batters and allowing just three hits and one walk.
James Wood hit his ninth homer of the season, contributing two runs for Washington.
Trea Turner hit a two-run homer to tie the game for the Phillies.
Washington Nationals responded with a four-run rally in the bottom of the eighth inning, keyed by James Wood’s leadoff triple.
Pre-Game Insights: Manager Dave Martinez emphasized the importance of MacKenzie Gore's strong finish to the season.
Post-Match Reflections: MacKenzie Gore reflected on his season, noting it was 'solid' overall despite some struggles.
Manager Dave Martinez praised Gore's performance and highlighted it as a great building block for the next season.
